title: Grateful Dead Live at Folsom Field, University of Colorado on 1972-09-03
description:
Disc #1:  Set One:  74:57

01. The Promised Land
02. Sugaree
03. Me And My Uncle
04. "Don't sit on that back wall..."
05. Tennessee Jed
06. Black Throated Wind
07. Bird Song
08. Beat It On Down The Line
09. Mississippi Half-Step
10. Playing In The Band
11. Casey Jones

Disc #2:  Set Two part 1:  53:09

01. Bertha 
02,03. El Paso
04. Brown Eyed Women
05. Mexicali Blues
06. China Cat Sunflower > 
07. I Know You Rider
08. Truckin'
09. Loser

Disc #3:  Set Two part 2:  56:06
01. Crowd/tuning
02. He's Gone >
03. The Other One >
04. Wharf Rat
05. Johnny B. Goode
06. "We're gonna take another break..."

Disc #4:  Set Three:  62:03

01. //Cold Rain And Snow 
02. Sugar Magnolia
03. Crowd/tuning
04. Deal
05. Jack Straw
06. Ramble On Rose
07. Rockin' Pneumonia & The Boogie Woogie Flu
08. Not Fade Away >
09. Goin' Down The Road Feeling Bad >
10. Not Fade Away

The band is still on stage when the tape breaks off.  
There must have been at least one more tune.

reviews.review_text: thank you Really nice 'Chinacat Sunflower' w/ a great 'I Know You Rider! Sound switches to SBD at 'Playing in the Band' and stays decent enough through NFA. first 9 songs are terrible. Sounds like it was a great show to be at. They played Berkeley, Eugene and Boulder in a little over a weeks time.... Good Vibrations

Correct day or no... Sick show, one of the best Casey Jones I've heard in a while...makes me want to sing "DRIVIN' THAT TRAIN, HIGH ON COCAINE!!!" At the top of my lungs, thought i'm sitting in a library right now...LOL Good sound quality for the era...5 stars cuz anything less would be misleading.

- Although the first set sound is real rough, this treatment is an improvement on the previous uploaded version. And the second set is just freakin crystal. Wild, exciting show, elegantly played, with 2nd set sound like a clear bronze bell.

Long show! It was a hot day and the Dead played and including their break the time ran around 7 hours. As I waited to get in one gate a gut started scaling the flagstone portals. He made it to the top where hands reached to help him over but they did not connect and he fell. Landing just a few feet from me onto hot asphalt (better than concrete) it was a sickening sound. He was tossed into an ambulance and I proceeded into the stadium just as Me and My Uncle began. At songs end Bob Weir announces to those up in the high seats to be careful as someone had fallen off but Bob did not know what actually happened.

The show was great despite the heat.

inferior source This tape should be taken down.  It is seriously inferior to the GEMS composite SBD + AUD posted elsewhere.  Don't waste your time, insult your ears & the Dead's music by listening to this.
